        <updateDate>2009-06-19T14:05:06Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Science Accountability Act of 2009 - Amends the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965 to require states to: (1) establish challenging academic content and student achievement standards in science, beginning in the 2010-2011 school year; and (2) measure the achievement of students in grades three through eight against such standards, beginning in the 2011-2012 school year.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
